definitions.definition: To make a difficult but successful return of the ball.
To remedy the evil consequence of, to repair (a loss or damage).
An instance of exhibiting.
That which is exhibited.
A public showing; an exhibition.
definitions.example: The museum's new exhibit is drawing quite a crowd.

definitions.definition: An article formally introduced as evidence in a court.
definitions.example: Exhibit A is this photograph of the corpse.

definitions.definition: To display or show (something) for others to see, especially at an exhibition or contest.
definitions.example: He wanted to exhibit his baseball cards.

definitions.definition: To demonstrate.
definitions.example: The players exhibited great skill.

definitions.definition: To submit (a physical object) to a court as evidence.
definitions.example: I now exhibit this bloody hammer.

definitions.definition: To put on a public display.
definitions.example: Will you be exhibiting this year?

definitions.definition: To administer as a remedy.
definitions.example: to exhibit calomel

definitions.definition: In an official manner; according to official rules or regulations.
Thoroughly, completely.
definitions.example: That’s it! I’m officially outraged.

definitions.definition: An association or combination of businesses, financial institutions, or investors, for the purpose of engaging in a joint venture.
A similar arrangement among non-commercial institutions or organizations.
An association or society.
The right of a spouse to all the normal relationships with his or her mate.
A group of symbiotic microbes.
To stop living; to become dead; to undergo death.
To (stop living and) undergo (a specified death).
definitions.example: He died a hero's death.

definitions.definition: To yearn intensely.
definitions.example: I'm dying for a packet of crisps.

definitions.definition: To be or become hated or utterly ignored or cut off, as if dead.
definitions.example: The day our sister eloped, she died to our mother.

definitions.definition: To become spiritually dead; to lose hope.
definitions.example: He died a little inside each time she refused to speak to him.

definitions.definition: To be mortified or shocked by a situation.
definitions.example: If anyone sees me wearing this ridiculous outfit, I'll die.

definitions.definition: To be so overcome with emotion or laughter as to be incapacitated.
definitions.example: When I found out my two favorite musicians would be recording an album together, I literally planned my own funeral arrangements and died.

definitions.definition: (of a machine) To stop working, to break down.
definitions.example: My car died in the middle of the freeway this morning.

definitions.definition: (of a computer program) To abort, to terminate (as an error condition).
To perish; to cease to exist; to become lost or extinct.
To sink; to faint; to pine; to languish, with weakness, discouragement, love, etc.
(often with "to") To become indifferent; to cease to be subject.
definitions.example: to die to pleasure or to sin

definitions.definition: To disappear gradually in another surface, as where mouldings are lost in a sloped or curved face.
To become vapid, flat, or spiritless, as liquor.
(of a stand-up comedian or a joke) To fail to evoke laughter from the audience.
definitions.example: Then there was that time I died onstage in Montreal...

definitions.definition: To colour with dye, or as if with dye.
The cubical part of a pedestal; a plinth.
A device for cutting into a specified shape.
A device used to cut an external screw thread. (Internal screw threads are cut with a tap.)
A mold for forming metal or plastic objects.
An embossed device used in stamping coins and medals.
(plural also dice) An oblong chip fractured from a semiconductor wafer engineered to perform as an independent device or integrated circuit.
Any small cubical or square body.
A colourant, especially one that has an affinity to the substrate to which it is applied.
Any hue, color, or blee.
A platform that extends outwards from a building.
A raised, flat-topped bank of earth with sloping sides, especially one of a series for farming or leisure; a similar natural area of ground, often next to a river.
A row of residential houses with no gaps between them; a group of row houses.
A single house in such a group.
(in the plural) The standing area at a football ground.
(chiefly Indian English) The roof of a building, especially if accessible to the residents. Often used for drying laundry, sun-drying foodstuffs, exercise, or sleeping outdoors in hot weather.
To provide something with a terrace.
To form something into a terrace.
A type, species, or strain of bacterium.
A derisive term for a lowlife or a slob (could be treated as plural or singular).
A single celled organism with cell walls but no nucleus or organelles.
An oval bacterium, as distinguished from a spherical coccus or rod-shaped bacillus.
To give a written or spoken response, especially to a question, request, accusation or criticism; to answer.
To act or gesture in response.
definitions.example: Joanne replied to Pete's insult with a slap to his face.

definitions.definition: To repeat something back; to echo.
Fish, shellfish, seaweed, and other edible aquatic life.
A work of prose fiction, longer than a novella.
A fable; a short tale, especially one of many making up a larger work.
A novelty; something new.
A new legal constitution in ancient Rome.
